{
  "stem": "24814.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I can remember the night the Germans did something stupid.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's always fun to think about.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They somehow got the word that we had retreated all the way to the Vosges Mountains.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were down near the Rhine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they came marching in, columns of fours, yelling commands right into our machine guns.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And our tanks went out there and they were screaming, Doc, Doc, get up here, get up here!",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was trying to get my ambulance toward the battle through a column of tanks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember the fireworks flaring and the shells going off.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Suddenly we were winning a battle, a very large one.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the hairiest part of that battle was the afternoon-- the day-- our last day on the line was the 19th of January in that battle.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The Germans counterattacked with 50 tanks, Tiger tanks mostly, big ones, came right across the plain toward our command post.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we were all watching through field glasses.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Our tanks were over on the other flank of the bridgehead, so there was nothing out there except a few machine gunners.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we-- our artillery observers called down artillery, and they knocked out some of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And our little headquarters detachment was out there with his one bazooka and a few machine guns and carbines to try and stop the 10th SS Panzer Division.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And just in the nick of time, our tank battalion came roaring from the other flank, went out there and took them on and drove them off.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "The Rhine fog came in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "There was a very tense thing that afternoon.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "That night we beat it off.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The Germans veered off to the south, and one of-- another battalion of our tanks caught them in what we called defilade.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
